üÖ∞Ô∏è Option A: Host Nginx + SSL (Certbot host)

Install Nginx in ec2
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y nginx certbot python3-certbot-nginx
```

Start the Services
```bash
docker-compose up -d --build
```

Create the Nginx Config
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name example.com www.example.com;

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3000;   # frontend container
    }

    location /api/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;   # backend container
    }
}
```

Enable & Reload
```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/enterprise /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

SSL Certificate
```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d example.com -d www.example.com
```


